rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0006
rows.name: Boss, you've got some impressive skills.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0007
rows.name: That's what I'd expect from a salvager!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0009
rows.name:
Your salvaging experience
must be coming in handy!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0010
rows.name:
I appreciate the compliments, but
we should get going to rescue Nia.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0011
rows.name: Boss, do you struggle with games?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0012
rows.name:
H-hey, give me a break...
It was my first attempt,
what do you expect?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0013
rows.name:
You'll definitely improve
with more practice.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0014
rows.name:
L-let's just
concentrate on Nia right now.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0001
rows.name:
How do we get to that Divine Beast
battleship where they're keeping Nia?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0002
rows.name:
From here, go up the stairs all the way,
cross the bridge, go through the gate,
and you'll arrive at Garagorm's Arch.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0003
rows.name:
Will we have trouble with
the Superbian Empire's guards?

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0004
rows.name:
Area around Superbian base heavily
guarded, but up to Garagorm's Arch
should be no problem!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0005
rows.name: Alright, let's aim for there first!

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0016
rows.name:
As luck would have it, the Cloud Sea
looks to be ebbing just now. We had
best aim for the root Homura mentioned.

rows.label: fev02_290_125_msg0017
rows.name:
Those roots were stretching out
just past Garagorm's Arch!
